{"word":"τρίβων","slug":"τρίβων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τρίβων</b></el> <el>(τρίβων, ονος, ὁ, ἡ,) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <i>practised</i> or <i>skilled in</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <i>a hackneyed, crafty fellow, rogue</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}